-- U.K. Water Offsetting Infrastructure Spending Slump, Report Says
-- B y   R a n d a l l   H a c k l e y
-- 2012-07-27T11:31:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-27/u-k-water-offsetting-infrastructure-spending-slump-report-says.html
The U.K. water and waste treatment
industry is bucking a slump in infrastructure upgrades in other
construction areas by spending hundreds of millions of pounds on
maintenance and improvements, according to a new report.  The WaterBriefing report on the 2010-2015 asset management
plan said British water and sewage companies are busy trying to
meet the demands of a growing population and climate change as
well as stiffer European Union environmental standards.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Hackley in Zurich at 
